---
import Layout from "@layouts/Default.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Punith R"
  description="Software engineer. 8 years shipping software. Now exploring product ideas, automations, and whatever I find interesting."
>
  <main class="home-redesign page-surface flex-grow border-b-[12px] border-frame">
    <h1 class="sr-only">Punith R — Software Engineer exploring Product</h1>

    <section class="home-hero" id="hero">
      <div class="home-hero__copy">
        <p class="home-kicker">Software engineer / product tinkerer / India</p>
        <h2>
          <span class="home-hero__name">This is Punith.</span>
          I bridge engineering and product to make complex ideas simple.
        </h2>
        <p class="home-hero__lede">
          I spent 8 years shipping software. Now I’m using that engineering muscle to explore AI workflows, product strategy, and practical ideas for Indian markets.
        </p>
      </div>

    </section>

    <section class="home-section home-section--cases" id="work">
      <div class="home-section__heading">
        <p class="home-section-label">Case files</p>
        <h2>Deep product teardowns, interactive prototypes, and zero hand-waving.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="home-case-grid">
        <a href="/blog/urban-company-teardown/" class="home-case home-case--urban">
          <div class="home-case__meta">
            <span>PRD / Live prototype</span>
            <span>Urban Company</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Multi-actor orchestration for remote home services</h3>
          <p>
            SMS bridge, smart repair buffer, and fail-safe approval loops for NRIs and remote property owners.
          </p>
          <!-- <div class="home-case__tags">
            <span>Product</span>
            <span>Service ops</span>
            <span>Prototype</span>
          </div> -->
        </a>

        <a href="/blog/proofit-prd/" class="home-case home-case--proofit">
          <div class="home-case__meta">
            <span>PRD / Live prototype</span>
            <span>ProofIt</span>
          </div>
          <h3>A credibility layer for Bangalore’s nano-vendors</h3>
          <p>
            A profile, vouch, and verification loop for micro businesses that close deals through WhatsApp.
          </p>
          <!-- <div class="home-case__tags">
            <span>B2B</span>
            <span>Trust</span>
            <span>India</span>
          </div> -->
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="home-section home-lab" id="lab">
      <div class="home-lab__main">
        <p class="home-section-label">What I’m up to</p>
        <h2>Small automations, useful prototypes, and ideas that refuse to stay in Notes.app.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="home-lab__grid">
        <article class="home-lab-card home-lab-card--yellow">
          <span>Automation</span>
          <h3>Reddit → AI summary → LinkedIn</h3>
          <p>Daily product-management signals turned into a draftable post.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="home-lab-card home-lab-card--mint">
          <span>Automation</span>
          <h3>Newsletters → AI digest → Discord</h3>
          <p>A low-friction way to keep up without pretending inbox zero is real.</p>
        </article>
        <article id="this-website-card" class="home-lab-card home-lab-card--black cursor-pointer">
          <span>This site</span>
          <h3>Neo-brutal shell, calmer inner rooms</h3>
          <p>Visitor logging, terminal shell, custom PRD layouts, and a design system slowly finding its spine.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="home-manifesto" aria-label="Personal statement">
      <p>
        I don’t have it all figured out.
        <span>But I’m building while I figure it out.</span>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="home-backstory" id="backstory">
      <div>
        <p class="home-section-label">Backstory</p>
        <h2>An engineer first, with a product brain.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="home-backstory__body">
        <p>
          I’ve spent the last 8 years building software, from trading platforms to UI systems used across engineering teams.
        </p>
        <p>
          After several years in the US, I moved back to India. I’m interested in AI, products, and the messy, high-leverage problems that affect millions of people here.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
